Paper-Cleaner is an AGGREGATE of independently licensed components. This MIT
license applies ONLY to the top-level glue authored in this repository:

    run.sh
    scripts/
    README.md, NOTICE, and the other top-level docs

The bundled subprojects are licensed separately and retain their own terms —
see NOTICE and each subdirectory's LICENSE file:

    arxiv-latex-cleaner/   Apache License 2.0     (The Google Research Authors)
    FactReview/            GNU AGPL v3.0          (FactReview authors)
    FactReview/RefCopilot/ GNU AGPL v3.0          (inherits FactReview/LICENSE)

Nothing here relicenses those components. The two subprojects are run as
independent programs (the glue only shells out to their CLIs and reads their
output files), so this bundle is a "mere aggregation" and each component keeps
its upstream license.

